I have always been interested in native American art, history and culture.
The museum is a nice size and can be walked in an afternoon.
I bought a membership so that I can go a few more times.
I was amazed by the diversity of artists and tribes represented at the museum.
In one gallery, there was an exhibit by an Inuit artist.
In another gallery, there was an exhibition by a Navajo metal smith and jewelry maker.
There is a great blending of the ancient native world with the modern native culture.
I was going to bypass the interactive displays for the children, but found as I walked them that they were meaningful for adults too.
Don't miss the Kachina display or the very sad and moving installation about the native American schools where young people were taken to be "civilized".

